,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT><BR><img src=http://www.battle.net/images/battle/diablo2/images/animations/bestiary/act1/Andariel.gif width=175  length=200></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">AOE group - what does the bard do?</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial"><br>
Numerous people have mentioned bards being good in AOE groups.<br>
<br>
I was wondering what the BARD'S strategy in it was? I have a L52 wizzie, and L53 bard... so I'm all about getting my Bard into an AOE group. (Will wait till both are L54 probably, maybe L55).<br>
<br>
I mean, I get the basic premise. The bard uses AOE slow/snare to pull... and runs around grabing mobs. Seems like an easy concept for pulling... and I know how to pull. The only thing I'd want to know is if there's an easy way to pull withou ttaking much damage?<br>
<br>
Second, what other songs should I be using?  Mana song for down time... on the pull, use the snare/slow. But during the fight, what should I be using? 1 weave of AOE DOT, and 2 weaves of AOE snare/slow (resists)? <br>
<br>
Any help would be appreciated. : )<br>
<br>
-Cueller</font><P><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#000000><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uranthrathan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ranthrathan</A></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Forum Wizard</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#ffffff>5/4/01</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#ffffff>10:15:38 am</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: AOE group - what does the bard do?</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">basically the bard plays manasong and kills singles should they pop.<br>
<br>
bard also plays aoe fear if enchanter falls to give wizards time to evacuate the group out.</font><P><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#33333><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ublastum.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Blastum</A></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Forum Apprentice</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#ffffff>5/4/01</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#ffffff>10:39:22 am</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Bards job...</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">  We have tested many bard songs, and found that the &quot;nods head&quot; song is almost useless, while the AE slow spell seems to take alot of the beatdown off the chanter.<br>
<br>
  In addition, the AE group with a bard has a very fast recharge time ( 2 forms of mana regen during downtime of course ).  This is an important factor if your AE group has many more mobs than they can clear in one spawn sequence.  For instance, sebilis at 4 am on a weeknight when all camps are available (or nearly so).  We have used a bard in such a case , and a single AE group cleared discofront/discoback/guardian/jail/bridge/zoneout/zonein  before the 28 min repop on the camp we started on.  This would be a nearly impossible feat of volume without the bard. <br>
<br>
In places like karnors, where Selo's will work, the bard makes a very good puller ( running through the castle singing AE damage song ) and with buffs the bard should have enough HP's to pull a nice sized train.<br>
<br>
<br>
Zzapp 60 Wizard and AE advocate</font><P><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#000000><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ueqkoikeeper.showPublicProfile?language=EN>EQKoikeeper</A></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Forum Apprentice</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#ffffff>5/4/01</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#ffffff>10:53:23 am</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT><BR><img src=http://www.prexus.com/harmonyofsouls/pics/hos_icon.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: Bards job...</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">What Blasum said... <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Slow songs can take the wind out of a mob's sails. </font><P><center><a href="http://www.prexus.com/harmonyofsouls"><IMG ALIGN=center BORDER=0 SRC="http://www.prexus.com/harmonyofsouls/pics/sigkoi3.gif"></a></center><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#33333><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uglomfyrestormm.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Glom Fyrestormm</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif BORDER=0></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Forum Wizard</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#ffffff>5/4/01</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#ffffff>12:54:28 pm</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: Bards job...</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial"><br>
I am not a bard so I may have the songs wrong, but I think the best  twist is:<br>
<br>
Selo`s Assonant Strane<br>
Denon`s Bereavement<br>
Cantana of Replenishment<br>
<br>
